              "coded_information": {
                "nuclide": "8-O-18",
                "field_identifier": "ENR",
                "value": 0.004
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Targets were prepared by",
                "anodization of 0.3 mm thick tantalum backings using",
                "H2O enriched in 17-O. Anodization produced",
                "homogeneous films of Ta2O5.The target thickness was",
                "chosen to be about 12 keV for an alpha particle beam",
                "of 1000 keV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "A HPGe detector with an efficiency of 55% with",
                "respect to NaI at 1333 keV was set up at an angle of",
                "45deg with respect to the beam axis. To reduce the",
                "radiation damage from the strong 17-O(alpha,n)20Ne",
                "channel, a polyethylene disk 8.3 cm in diameter and",
                "2.0 cm thick was attached to the front cap of the",
                "detector to scatter reaction neutrons away from the",
                "HPGe detector."
              ]
            }
